title A root README in the generic Acme voice, a root contributor profile, the warm-aura versioning synthesis, and the VPS hypervisor strategy
prompt Keaton asked to ensure context and foundations are adapted for the generic templated Acme Corporation employee, with personal/professional specifics loaded into a root Bron profile; to take inspiration from the gratitude Spec-ulation source for doc-code syncing and chronological versioning that fits a Glow warm aura for datetime adopted from Hoon/Arvo/Zuse; and to update the VM hosting strategy docs for the rish setup scripts and ai-jail (macOS or Linux host) connecting to VPS machines on whichever providers allow hypervisor runtimes for the Genode microkernel seam. Mid-turn, asked first for a new root README in the generic Acme voice highlighting the four Glow OS variants, then to continue. Model switched to Fable 5 1M Max for this turn.
think Explored before writing: found the four-variant framing already seated across manual/glow-os (overview, get-started, variants template) and the naming specs, so the README could highlight the four choices (Reya, Riyo, Trey, Triz) accurately rather than invent framing — one design built more than once for diverse redundancy, Reya/Riyo the confirmed pair, Trey/Triz pairing still open.
think Wrote the root README.md in the generic Acme voice (addressing you, never a named person), leading with the four choices as the template's central decision, then the honest top-to-bottom shape with per-row status, what actually runs today, and the two-file setup path. Allow-listed README.md and GLOW_PROFILE.template.bron in .gitignore, which otherwise ignores everything at root by default.
think For the profile: mirrored the GLOW_HOST.bron pattern exactly, which Keaton already established and likes — a committed GLOW_PROFILE.template.bron (generic values) plus a gitignored GLOW_PROFILE.bron (filled with Keaton's real identity). The root /* catch-all already ignores the filled copy; verified with git check-ignore. The profile carries name, forge handles, email, Azimuth points, clock, and session-log editor/model/voice defaults — and per root rule 9 (docs and implementation stay synced) it points at PUBKEYS.md for fingerprints rather than copying them, so the two records cannot drift.
think Seated the profile and the generic-voice decision in a spec, and adapted the living entry docs on-touch: fixed context/README.md's stale ~/veganreyklah2 workspace path to the Glow OS repo, added the profile line, generalized the reader address, migrated Kaeden to Keaton; migrated foundations/README.md's Kaeden to Keaton; added a GLOW_PROFILE.bron entry to ORGANIZING.md beside GLOW_HOST.bron. Kept it a ratchet, not a sweep — only the docs already open for this work.
think For the versioning synthesis, found the genuinely elegant fusion the prompt was reaching for: Spec-ulation's one idea (change is growth or breakage; accrete, never break; enduring names; the only truth is runtime) maps onto Hoon's warm/cold atom distinction. Warm = growth = the chronological YYYYMMDD.HHMMSS clock that counts up and accretes (Rye's already-decided scheme); cold = freeze = kelvin counting down to a frozen constant zero. Glow tells its own time as a warm date aura (grows, never breaks a shipped name) and pins kelvin as a cold external constant at the Urbit-facing seam. The same warm/cold lens then re-explains root rule 9: a doc's behavioral claim is warm (a suggestion, like a POM entry) until a green witness pins it cold (the only truth is runtime) — Two Rooms in aura terms. Wrote it as one doc because the two asks are one idea seen twice.
think For hosting: researched which VPS providers actually permit nested virtualization, since that is the real gap the Neth cost plan deferred. Found the organizing distinction — Neth replicas need NO nested virt (any VPS, already settled), but a KVM-accelerated Genode seam DOES (or bare metal). Confirmed Hetzner/OVH standard cloud do not expose nested virt (dedicated lines do), AWS does on specific instance families, Cloudzy and SSD Nodes expose /dev/kvm directly and cheaply. Framed the full path plainly: host inside its enclosure (macOS sandbox-exec OR Linux ai-jail, named as siblings) reaches the VPS over the existing WireGuard tunnel (rish client half, bash server half), and the Genode seam runs accelerated only on a nested-virt-enabling or dedicated box. Named the next rish provisioner script honestly as gated on a real nested-virt VPS to witness against, rather than stubbing it ahead of the metal.
think Did not re-edit the dated Neth cost plan (sealed on main); the new hosting-strategy doc accretes beside it and cites it as builds-on, which satisfies the docs-sync discipline without touching a dated artifact. Verified every load-bearing path the new docs cite actually exists on disk before finishing, per rule 9.
obs The warm/cold-aura framing is the real find of this turn: it resolves what looked like a contradiction (chronological-up versus kelvin-down) into two honest states of one value, and it re-derives the brand-new doc-sync rule 9 from the same source, which is itself the discipline in action — one enduring idea accreted into a second place rather than two half-overlapping rules left to drift.
